why not just upgrade everything else?<br>
<br>
Some things in a game call for an upgrade of classes and some thing call for a nerf, usually it’s a well defined line of demarcation between the two.<br>
<br>
In beta, Archers were God up until a point(and I believe I posted about this here before). They get a critical shot ability that gives them a multiplier of damage and they also get the hide skill that renders them almost completely invisible, totally invisible at a distance. So archers would roam the battlefield, or stand in one place, completely unseen and just snipe people. It doesn’t sound all that bad, pretty neat actually, but the broken aspect was that hiding was instantaneous. Meaning, Archer would snipe someone and appear for a split second before going inviso again. Even if you managed to target him in that brief instant, you lost the target when he went into sneak mode again. Insta-hide was very, very broken and no amount of buffing to other classes would have brought it in line.<br>
<br>
An email went from me to Sanya to Marc Jacobs and sneak gained a 10-second reuse time in the next patch. They’re still hella-powerful, they just have to put more thought into where they shoot from instead of standing in an open field while mowing people down. <br>
Vendrix<br>
Da`Kor<br>
